bilingual.source: Think of a name for your newspaper.
Were the five things in the newspaper?
bilingual.target: 这五件事都在报纸上吗？

bilingual.source: Did Mark Twain become a newspaper writer?
bilingual.target: 马克·吐温成为报纸作家了吗？

bilingual.source: Chen gave an interview to the local newspaper.
bilingual.target: 陈接受了当地报纸的采访。

bilingual.source: What job would you like to have on a newspaper?
bilingual.target: 你想在报纸上做什么工作？

list.abstract: newspaper（英[ˈnjuːzpeɪpə]，美[ˈnuːzpeɪpər]），英语单词，名词，译为报纸；报。短语搭配有newspaper article（报纸文章）。例句为“Cherish the newspaper still in your hand.（珍惜你手中的报纸。）” 该单词名词的近义词为paper、courant，复数形式为newspapers。

yingyinNormal.en: Daddy, we need your newspaper. What for? Making paper aeroplanes.
yingyinNormal.zh: 爸爸，可以把你的报纸给我们吗？干什么。我们想用你的报纸来折纸飞机。

yingyinNormal.en: Daddy, we need your newspaper. What for? Making paper aeroplanes.
yingyinNormal.zh: 爸爸，可以把你的报纸给我们吗。干什么。我们想用你的报纸来折纸飞机。哦呵呵哈哈。

yingyinNormal.en: I mean, really, USA Today, that's the nice newspaper.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我就纳闷了《今日美国》这样的好报纸居然也这样。

yingyinNormal.en: Actually, I think there's something about George in this newspaper.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你来看看，这报纸上好像有点关于乔治的消息。

yingyinNormal.en: Can you find a newspaper for the red box? George wants to recycle Daddy Pig's newspaper.
yingyinNormal.zh: 找份放进红色箱子的报纸?乔治想回收爸爸的报纸。

yingyinNormal.en: Can you find a newspaper for the red box? George wants to recycle Daddy Pig's newspaper.
yingyinNormal.zh: 找份放进红色箱子的报纸?乔治想回收爸爸的报纸。

yingyinNormal.en: Do you need anything from the shops? Maybe a newspaper, and comic Newspaper, comic.
yingyinNormal.zh: 需要帮你们从超市带点什么吗。也许我需要一份报纸吧，还有漫画。一份报纸，漫画。

yingyinNormal.en: Daddy pig is reading his newspaper. You could have my newspaper when I finish reading it. All right. Hooray. Now we can start painting.
yingyinNormal.zh: 猪爸爸正在看报纸。等我看完了报纸你们就可以拿去用了。看好！好嘞！现在我们可以开始画画啦！

yingyinNormal.en: We need some old newspaper to put on the table. Yes.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们需要在餐桌上放一些旧的报纸。没错。

yingyinNormal.en: It is a lovely sunny morning. And Daddy Pig is reading his newspaper.
yingyinNormal.zh: 今天是个阳光明媚的早晨。猪爸爸正在看他的报纸。

yingyinNormal.en: Daddy Pig is in the sitting room, reading his newspaper. Mummy Pig is reading her book.
yingyinNormal.zh: 猪爸爸在客厅里面看报纸。猪妈妈在看书。

yingyinNormal.en: I haven't finished with my newspaper just yet, George. You can have it in a minute.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我的报纸还没看完不能给你，乔治。你得等一下。

yingyinNormal.en: Mine stole my newspaper. It's like a crime wave. Pheebs, you got a second? Sure.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我的邻居偷走我的报纸，这简直是犯罪潮，菲比，你有空吗？当然有。

yingyinNormal.en: Cheese. Thank you, Peppa. You are a good... Newspaper and comic. Thanks, Peppa.
yingyinNormal.zh: 奶酪来了，谢谢佩奇，你真是个好孩子。报纸还有漫画。谢谢你，佩奇。

yingyinNormal.en: Daddy what are you doing? I'm reading the newspaper. You are making a funny sound.
yingyinNormal.zh: 爸爸，你在干什么呀？我正在看报纸呢。你怎么发出了很奇怪的声音啊。

yingyinNormal.en: Rebecca Rabbit does not have a boat. I've got an idea. Luckily I've brought my newspaper along.
yingyinNormal.zh: 小腿瑞贝卡没有船。我有一个主意。我真好带了我的报纸过来。

yingyinNormal.en: Daddy Pig is going to read his newspaper. What a nice day for doing nothing. Daddy Pig loves doing nothing.
yingyinNormal.zh: 猪爸爸准备要看报纸了。今天天真好，真该什么都不做。

yingyinNormal.en: When I was a little piggy, I used to fold newspaper like this. What is Daddy Pig doing? To make a paper boat. Daddy Pig has made a paper boat. Thank you, Mr. Pig.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我记得在我小时候，我经常会用报纸做手工 就像这样。猪爸爸要做什么？我要做一艘船。猪爸爸用报纸做了一艘纸船。谢谢你，猪爸爸。

yingyinNormal.en: I haven't finished with my newspaper just yet, George. You can have it in a minute. Oh, all right. Here you are, George.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我的报纸还没看完不能给你，乔治。你得等一下。看完了。拿去吧，乔治。

yingyinNormal.en: Peppa and George are looking for Daddy's glasses. Peppa looks under the newspaper. But Daddy Pig's glasses are not there. Oh.
yingyinNormal.zh: 佩奇和乔治开始帮爸爸找眼镜了，佩奇找了报纸底下，但是爸爸的眼镜不在这。噢。

数据源自2016.6-2023.6年8年间全六级试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>

examination_example.sentence: 49 years later, Apollo 11 reached the moon, and the famed <highlight>newspaper</highlight> published an apology to Goddard.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 49年后，阿波罗11号到达月球，这家著名的报纸发表了对Goddard的道歉。

examination_example.sentence: Indeed, within minutes the fire occupied headlines of every major global <highlight>newspaper</highlight> and television network.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 确实，几分钟之内，大火占据了全球各大报纸和电视网络的头条。

examination_example.sentence: Two months before he died, <highlight>newspapers</highlight> were reporting that he was working on a "death ray".
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在他去世前两个月，报纸报道他正在研究“死亡射线”。

examination_example.sentence: For today's youth, books, <highlight>newspapers</highlight> and magazines have less and less of a presence in their daily lives.

examination_example.sentence_trans: 值得注意的是，这不仅仅是纸质书籍、报纸或杂志阅读量的下降。

examination_example.sentence: It meant any inexpensive <highlight>newspaper</highlight>; perhaps more importantly it meant newspapers that could be bought in single copies on the street.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这意味着任何便宜的报纸；也许更重要的是，这意味着报纸可以在街上买到。

examination_example.sentence: When I came to the US, I was only thinking about being a carpenter, but I could not read the <highlight>newspaper</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当我来到美国时，我只想当一名木匠，但我看不懂报纸。

examination_example.sentence: I realized this a day later, when I saw <highlight>newspaper</highlight> advertisements for the set at seventy-five dollars less than I had paid.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一天后，当我看到报纸广告说这台电视机比我支付的价格低75美元时，我意识到了这一点。
